JUL 22 1992
DATE: 
 
 

REPLY TO 
 
 ATTN OF: Portland Area Director

SUBJECT: Confederated Tribes of the Warm Springs Reservation of Oregon 

Constitution Amendment No. XIV

TOl Deputy Commissioner - Indian Affairs 
Director, Division of Tribal Services 
MAILSTOP 2611 MIB

Attached for information is the approval of the Confederated Tribes of 

the Warm Springs Reservation of Oregon Constitution Amendment No. XIV

dated July 22, 1992. Also attached with it are the Certificate of 

Results of Election, Approval by the Acting Portland Area Director, 

Amendment A, and the Official Ballot. Amendment A is now renumbered 

Amendment XIV, Article III - Salaries. If you have any questions, please 

contact James Rogers, Tribal Government Services, at (503) 231-6723.
 
  
 

AMENDMENT 
CONSTITUTION AND BYLAWS 
 
 of the 
 
CONFEDERATED TRIBES OF THE WARM SPRINGS 
RESERVATION OF OREGON


 
  
 AMENDMENT NO. XIV 
 

ARTICLE III - SALARIES

 
 Tribal Council members shall receive as compensation for their services 

not to exceed $50 while in session for up to four hours per day and 

$12.50 per hour thereafter while in session, but not to exceed $100 per 

day total compensation, and mileage from home to place of meeting and 

return at a rate used by the federal government. Expenses shall be paid 

from available tribal funds. The Tribal Council may establish salaries 

of officer and committee members.
 
 

CERTIFICATE OF RESULTS OF ELECTION

 
 Pursuant to an election authorized by the Area Director, Portland 

Area Office, Bureau of Indian Affairs on April 29, 1992 (and 

reauthorized on June 2, 1992, the attached Amendment A to the 

Constitution and Bylaws of the Confederated Tribes of Warm Springs, 

was submitted to the qualified voters of the Confederated Tribes of 

Warm Springs membership and on July 13, 1992, was duly adopted 

rejected by a vote of 84 FOR, 40 AGAINST, ABSTENTIONS

and 1 CAST BALLOTS FOUND SPOILED OR MUTILATED, in an election 

in which at least 30% of the 291 entitled to vote, cast their 

ballots in accordance with Section 16 of the Indian Reorganization

Act of June 18, 1934 (48 Stat. 984), as amended by the Act of June 

15, 1935 (49 Stat. 378) .

7/13/92

Date
 
 

APPROVAL

 
 I, Portland Area Director, Bureau of Indian Affairs, Portland, Oregon, by 

virtue of the authority granted to the Secretary of the Interior of the 

United States, by the Act of June 18, 1934 (48 Stat. 984), as amended, 

and delegated to me by 10 BIAM, Section 2, Release 44, February 18, 1989, 

incorporating 230 DM Release No. 2784 dated March 16, 1988, do hereby 

approve the foregoing Amendment to the Constitution and Bylaws of the 

Confederated Tribes of the Warm Springs Reservation of Oregon. This 

amendment was adopted by a majority of the qualified voters of the said 

Confederated Tribes of the Warm Springs Reservation of Oregon voting on 

July 13, 1992.

DATE: July 13, 1992
 
 

REPLY TO
 
 ATTN OF: Reservation Programs, Warm Springs Agency

SUBJECT: Confederated Tribes of Warm Springs Constitutional 

Amendment Election held July 13, 1992

TO: Area Director, Portland Area

ATTN: Tribal Government Services

The results of the Confederated Tribes of Warm Springs 
Constitutional Amendment Election is as follows:

AMENDMENT A:YES 84 NO 40 ABSTENTIONS 0 SPOILED 1

The original amendments and completed Certificates of 
Results of Election will be mailed today.

Attachments
 
  
 

OFFICIAL BALLOT

CONFEDERATED TRIBES OF THE WARM SPRINGS

RESERVATION OF OREGON

 
 QUESTION; 
 

SHOULD THE CONSTITUTION OF THE CONFEDERATED TRIBES OF THE WARM 

 
  
 SPRINGS INDIAN RESERVATION OF OREGON BE AMENDED TO READ AS FOLLOWS: 
 

ARTICLE III - SALARIES

 
 Tribal Council members shall receive as compensation for their 
services not to exceed $50 while in session for up to four 
hours per day and $12.50 per hour thereafter while in session, 
but not to exceed $100 per day total compensation, and mileage 
from home to place of meeting and return at a rate used by the 
federal government. Expenses shall be paid from available 
tribal funds. The Tribal Council may establish salaries of 
officer and committee members.
 
 

YES

NO

 
 